The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, specifically private information retrieval (PIR) codes and batch codes. These topics are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
